Trim matrix:

More detailed configuration here, but this is a post requiring cookie and an ss request paramater
https://www.chevrolet.com/byo-vc/services/retrieveConfiguration/chevrolet/US/en/na/420658?bodystyle=spark&carline=spark&modelyear=2022&postalCode=94102

ss stands for serialized-state.  Seems to be a way to send the configuration to the backend or pull the configuration.

model apis

# Listing of features
https://www.chevrolet.com/byo-vc/services/features-specs/comparison/en/US/chevrolet/silverado/2022/silverado-3500hd
# Standard features
/byo-vc/api/v2/standard-features/en/US/chevrolet/silverado/2022/silverado-3500hd/421102

https://www.chevrolet.com/byo-vc/api/v2/trim-matrix/en/US/chevrolet/spark/2020/spark?postalCode=94102
# https://www.chevrolet.com/byo-vc/api/v2/trim-matrix/en/US/chevrolet/{carLine}/2020/{bodyStyle}?postalCode={postalCode} note: postal code optional, but prices significantly higher w/o
https://www.chevrolet.com/byo-vc/services/fullyConfigured/US/en/chevrolet/2022/silverado/silverado-3500hd?postalCode=94102&region=na # seems to provide more info than trim matrix


#model list to model name
https://www.chevrolet.com/bypass/gmna/saleslead/AjaxupdateSelection?carlineAvailable=false&outputType=json&configRepresentation=bodySelection&x-country=US&x-language=en&x-brand=chevrolet&x-requestType=requestQuoteSingleForm&channel=b2c&featureSelection=modelyear.2022%3Csep%2F%3E

carline is like a brand family, body style a specific type from the family
carline | bodystyle
corvette | corvette-z06
suburban | suburban-1500


